    "# Financial analysis"

   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from relife import Gompertz, AgeReplacementPolicy, OneCycleAgeReplacementPolicy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "af7b9bbb-ae24-40b9-b576-eff32b3e4e9c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(array([[ 7.82608906],\n",
       "        [ 9.06699905],\n",
       "        [19.02758643]]),\n",
       " array([[20.91316269],\n",
       "        [25.54310597],\n",
       "        [41.59988035]]))"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "a0 = np.array([15, 20, 25]).reshape(-1, 1)  # Ages initiaux des actifs\n",
    "cp = 10  # Cout d'un rempalcement préventif\n",
    "cf = np.array([900, 500, 100]).reshape(-1, 1)  # Cout d'un rempalcement sur défaillance\n",
    "discount_rate = 0.04  # taux d'actualisation\n",
    "\n",
    "distribution = Gompertz(shape=0.00391, rate=0.0758)  # Modèle de durée de vie des actifs\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remplacement par âge sur une infinité de cycles\n",
    "ar_policy = AgeReplacementPolicy(\n",
    "    distribution, cf=cf, a0=a0, cp=cp, discount_rate=discount_rate\n",
    ")\n",
    "ar_policy.fit(inplace=True)\n",
    "ar_policy.ar1, ar_policy.ar"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "816844e9-46b0-4289-9b4e-52c7f76e87d7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array([[ 7.82608906],\n",
       "       [ 9.06699905],\n",
       "       [19.02758643]])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Remplacement par âge sur un cycle\n",
    "onecycle_ar_policy = OneCycleAgeReplacementPolicy(\n",
    "    distribution, a0=a0, cf=cf, cp=cp, discount_rate=discount_rate\n",
    ")\n",
    "onecycle_ar_policy.fit(inplace=True)\n",
    "onecycle_ar_policy.ar"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "distrib = Gompertz(shape=0.2, rate=0.1)\n",
    "distrib.mean(), distrib.var()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "t = np.linspace(0, 100, num=1000)\n",
    "ax = distrib.plot.pdf(t, label=\"Distribution des durées de vie\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Age\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Densité\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "ar_policy = AgeReplacementPolicy(distrib, cf=cf, cp=cp, discount_rate=discount_rate)\n",
    "ar_policy.fit(inplace=True)\n",
    "optimal_ar = ar_policy.ar\n",
    "print(optimal_ar)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "05c3b9c1-35fc-4f71-acdd-4515f07ff936",

   ],
   "source": [
    "cp = 1\n",
    "cf = 5\n",
    "discount_rate = 0.05\n",
    "\n",
    "ar = np.arange(1, 100, 0.1).reshape(-1, 1)  # range of ar\n",
    "ar_policy = AgeReplacementPolicy(\n",
    "    distrib, cf=cf, cp=cp, ar=ar, discount_rate=discount_rate\n",
    ")\n",
    "za = ar_policy.asymptotic_expected_equivalent_annual_cost()\n",
    "ar_policy.fit(inplace=True)\n",
    "ar_opt = ar_policy.ar  # optimal ar\n",
    "za_opt = ar_policy.asymptotic_expected_equivalent_annual_cost()\n",
    "plt.plot(ar, za)\n",
    "plt.scatter(ar_opt, za_opt, label=f\" cf={cf} k€, ar={np.round(ar_opt, 2)} years\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Age of preventive replacement [years]\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Asymptotic expected equivalent annual cost [k€]\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"asymptotic expected equivalent annual cost with optimal ar :\", za_opt)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "source": [
    "dt = 0.5\n",
    "step = int(1 / dt)\n",
    "t = np.arange(0, 100 + dt, dt)\n",
    "z = ar_policy.expected_total_cost(t)\n",
    "y = t[::step][1:]\n",
    "q = np.diff(z[::step])\n",
    "plt.bar(2020 + y, q, align=\"edge\", width=-0.8, alpha=0.8, color=\"C2\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Year\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Expected discounted annual cost in k€\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

    "# Choix d'une stratégie de remplacement a priori, sans calcul d'optimalité.\n",
    "ar = 25\n",
    "# Projection des conséquences de la stratégie\n",
    "sub_opti_ar_policy = AgeReplacementPolicy(\n",
    "    distrib, cf=cf, cp=cp, ar=ar, discount_rate=discount_rate\n",
    ")\n",
    "# Cout de long terme de la stratégie\n",
    "print(sub_opti_ar_policy.asymptotic_expected_equivalent_annual_cost())\n",
    "# Distribution des coûts de la stratégie au cours du temps\n",
    "dt = 0.5\n",
    "step = int(1 / dt)\n",
    "t = np.arange(0, 100 + dt, dt)\n",
    "z = sub_opti_ar_policy.expected_total_cost(t)\n",
    "y = t[::step][1:]\n",
    "q = np.diff(z[::step])\n",
    "plt.bar(2020 + y, q, align=\"edge\", width=-0.8, alpha=0.8, color=\"C2\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Year\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Expected discounted annual cost in k€\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
